4.10	Edward_C._Elliott_Hall_of_Music	Elliott Hall of Music	The Edward C. Elliott Hall of Music is located on the Purdue University campus in West Lafayette, Indiana, USA. With a seating capacity of 6,005, it is one of the largest proscenium theaters in the world, and is about 100 seats larger than Radio City Music Hall. The facility is named after Edward C. Elliott (1874-1960), who served as President of Purdue University from 1922 to 1945. The stage of the hall is one of the largest in the country. It is roughly the same size as the stage of the Kodak Theater.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Hall_of_Music%2C_Purdue.JPG/200px-Hall_of_Music%2C_Purdue.JPG
